{"tid":996792,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"委內瑞拉總統想向英國銀行提取價值12億美元既黃金 英國佬係美帝遊說下拒絕","createTime":"2019-01-26T14:49:41.000Z","updateTime":"2019-02-08T06:19:24.000Z","uid":48083,"like":75,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":46,"replies":[{"pid":"b6d0f3ca9b054064e1206f4149f5721e544ff76a","tid":996792,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-01-26T14:49:41.000Z","msg":"Venezuela Wants $1.2 Billion in Gold Back From Bank of England<br />\nBy Patricia Laya  and Ethan Bronner<br />\n<br />\nJanuary 25, 2019, 2:11 PM EST<br />\n<br />\nU.S. lobbied U.K. officials to cut off the Maduro regime<br />\nEU takes sides against Maduro in Venezuela&rsquo;s power struggle<br />\n<br />\nNicolas Maduro&rsquo;s embattled Venezuelan regime, desperate to hold onto the dwindling cash pile it has abroad, was stymied in its bid to pull $1.2 billion worth of gold out of the Bank of England, according to people familiar with the matter.<br />\n<br />\nThe Bank of England&rsquo;s decision to deny Maduro officials&rsquo; withdrawal request comes after top U.S. officials, including Secretary of State Michael Pompeo and National Security Adviser John Bolton, lobbied their U.K. counterparts to help cut off the regime from its overseas assets, according to one of the people, who asked not to be identified.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/amp/news/articles/2019-01-25/u-k-said-to-deny-maduro-s-bid-to-pull-1-2-billion-of-gold?__twitter_impression=true\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Famp%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-01-25%2Fu-k-said-to-deny-maduro-s-bid-to-pull-1-2-billion-of-gold%3F__twitter_impression%3Dtrue&d=WN7QTdLR8ps8ZSj%2F63IP5Nr9upuAghWR75VkZoMWgf8%3D&h=9ebcfd15\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/amp/news/articles/2019-01-25/u-k-said-to-deny-maduro-s-bid-to-pull-1-2-billion-of-gold?__twitter_impression=true</a>"},{"pid":"b8f652520a081c162586ebede485b8bb9a029690","tid":996792,"uid":182499,"like":2,"dislike":1,"sc